<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,660,1407]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1200,1227]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Habitat:</emphasis>
Douglas fir forest and grama-needlegrass-wheatgrass grassland vegetation 
<typeStatus box="[1147,1210,1201,1227]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">types</typeStatus>
. Short- to mid-grass rangeland and moist mountainous valleys; swampy areas (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lavigne, R. J. &amp; Dennis, D. S." box="[848,1122,1236,1263]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="992 - 996" refId="ref105187" refString="Lavigne, R. J. &amp; Dennis, D. S. (1975) Ethology of Efferia frewingi (Diptera: Asilidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 68, 992 - 996. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 68.6.992" type="journal article" year="1975">Dennis &amp; Lavigne 1975</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,660,1407]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1273,1299]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Ethology:</emphasis>
Always foraged from twig tips of mountain gooseberry (
<taxonomicName authority="McClatchie" authorityName="McClatchie" box="[956,1303,1273,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Grossulariaceae" genus="Ribes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montigenum">
<emphasis box="[956,1163,1273,1299]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Ribes montigenum</emphasis>
McClatchie
</taxonomicName>
) 
<quantity box="[1317,1386,1272,1299]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="cm" value="52.0">52 cm</quantity>
to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
above the ground; courtship (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lavigne, R. J. &amp; Dennis, D. S." box="[552,826,1308,1335]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" pagination="992 - 996" refId="ref105187" refString="Lavigne, R. J. &amp; Dennis, D. S. (1975) Ethology of Efferia frewingi (Diptera: Asilidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 68, 992 - 996. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 68.6.992" type="journal article" year="1975">Dennis &amp; Lavigne 1975</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
